-----------------------------------------------
MedIOLib - Medical Data C++ I/O Library
-----------------------------------------------
// vim:set ts=2 nowrap:

$Id$
$Source$

2005-08-05  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * misc: initial port to Qt4 (still with Qt3Support) and separation of the
    CVS repository into two different branches for Qt3 and Qt4 development.
    (MAIN branch is the Qt4 one)

2005-07-14  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * CECATDirectoryItem.cpp: added check&code to enforce that a writeMatrix() call
    always ensures that full ECAT_BLOCKSIZE data is written. Previously, if a
    user passed a matrix/data size which is not divideable through ECAT_BLOCKSIZE,
    libmedio did exactly write the passed data size and as such violated the
    ECAT standard which defines that ECAT files have to be always a mulitple of
    ECAT_BLOCKSIZE data.

2005-07-06  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * m4/acinclude.m4: added gcc4 to supported GCC compiler versions.

2005-04-08  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * CECAT7MainHeader.cpp: implemented special QDateTime/QDate aware
    methods to deal with the time_t related date&time values specified
    in the ECAT format. These methods should make dealing with all that
    time_t mess a bit better as QDateTime seems not to be fully time_t
    aware as it defines time_t to be unsigned :(
	* m4/acinclude.m4: make configure deal with strangs GCC version strings.

2005-03-17  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * CECATDirectoryItem.cpp: fixed bug in the subHeader identification
    routines which caused that a writeMatrix() did always reset the
    subHeader of a file, even if a writeSubHeader() operation was done
    prior to it.

2005-03-07  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * CECATDirectoryItem.cpp: fixed bug in the writeMatrix(data, subHeader)
    sub methods where the supplied subHeader wasn't correctly written to
    the ECAT file.
  * CECAT7MainHeader.cpp: added Dose_Start_Time and plane number settings to
    default settings of the main Header.
	 
2005-03-02  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * misc: added a global operator= method to the MedIOHeader interface and
    made it call a pure virtual protected copyData() method. This way we force 
    classes to implement a proper protected copyData() method which then is
    used to copy data (shallow copy) out of one MedIOHeader object to the
    other one. However, please note that currently not all copy operations
    from one header typ to another one is supported. Especially all the
    Concorde<>ECAT copy implementations are missing.
  
2005-02-25  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * SubHeaders: the way ECAT Subheader were cached was done slightly wrong.
    Now the header should be successfully cached either on a save() or
    writeSubHeader() execution.
  * CECATFile.cpp: fixed bug in the mainHeaderWritten() method where upon an
    already existing mainHeader the data wasn't correctly copied out of it.
    This caused that on a writeMatrix() operation an already written
    mainHeader was abadoned.
  * libmedio.pro.in: added optimization level for the different host types
    found by configure.
  * CECATFile.cpp: fixed bug where upon usage of the IO_WriteOnly mode an
    existing file wasn't overwritten at all and the open() call returned
    false.

2005-02-04  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * examples/ecat/ecatcmp: added another small usefull example on how to use
    libmedio to read out an ECAT file. This utility can be quite handy if one
	 wants to compare two different ECAT files if they are the same.
	 It analyses some main Header, SubHeader and also directory list
	 information outputs there differences and also compares the raw matrix
	 data of each data item in the ECAT file.
  
2005-02-03  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * CECATDirectoryItem.cpp: fixed the hopefully last bug in the dataBlock_Ënd
    calculation which caused that libmedio wrote either too much or too less
	 data to the final ECAT file. Also added some more debug output to the
	 ECAT routines to be on the safe side in future.
  
2005-01-28  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * misc: adapted the debugging mechanism to use the new separated librtdebug
    debugging library instead of having it directly included in the project
    tree.
  
2005-01-25  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * misc: did some general adaptions to make MedIO work with lmmc again.
  * CECATFile.h: added additional createEmpty* methods to make it possible to
    easily create an empty MainHeader and SubHeaders which do conform to
    the actual file they were created on. However, please note that they might
    not just be used with their corresponging save() methods and have to be
    passed to one of the write() methods for correctly saving it to the file.

2005-01-24  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * CMedIOData.h: added errorStatus() method to allow to carry special error
    messages for our methods in future.
  
2005-01-21  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * misc: removed all additional "medio/" pathes from the include statements
    of our header files as a library doesn't have to contain any subdirectory
    statments and people should better use "-I/usr/local/lib/medio" in their
    makefiles.
  * misc: implemented/fixed the ECAT write methods in may way which were quite
    broken after the new redesign. Now also matrix­wise writing seems to work
    fine so that a user might save different matrices at any time without
    having to care about the order.
  
2005-01-17  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * misc: checked in some fixes that prevented the ECAT reading routines from
    working after the big change.
    Also removed the default values for the frame in all main methods.

2004-12-07  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * misc: reworked the whole MedIO API to be somewhat more consistent. Dropped
    the load/save methods and replaced them by proper open/close methods that
    have to be used like normal QFile objects. Also renamed the get/set
    Matrix/Subheader methods to read/write methods which all return bool now
    and if a new object like a subheader or mainheader or even raw matrix data
    is created the data is not shared with the MedIO library anymore, which
    previously caused some troubles when a return matrix data was freed by the
    user.
    Also adapted the ECAT file format to the new API of the MedIO library and
    started to implement some faster read/write methods that are automatically
    buffered by QByteArray objects.
    Also bumped the version of libmedio to 0.2 and tagged the old version in the
    cvs as "ALPHA_0_1".
    
    NOTE: Please note, however, that this is still work in progress, which
    means that the Concorde I/O routines are currently disabled until they are
    ported to the new API and that the new ECAT file I/O routines should be
    considered experimentel and not finished. They need some more work until they
    can be used in normal applications like the previous routines.
    
2004-10-04  Hagen Mölle <draggore@gmx.de>

  * added concorde micropet image support - possibility to load image files

2004-09-30  Frank Hofheinz <f.hofheinz@fz-rossendorf.de>

  * CECATFile.cpp: completed switch in 'setFileType(...)'
  * CECATFile.cpp, CECATFile.h: added size of array in call of 'setMatrixData(...)'
  
2004-09-29  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * CECAT7SubHeaderImage.h: fixed minor typo in z_pixel_size get method.
  
2004-09-28  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * misc: added all missing accessor methods to all kind of ECAT7 subheaders and
    also implemented copy constructors for all of them. Now the ECAT7 support should
    be more or less complete. Only ECAT6 is missing to have a complete ECAT suite.
  
2004-09-24  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * CECAT7MainHeader.h: the patient birthdate was specified as a "unsigned int"
    which was slightly wrong as the ECAT format specifies date prior to 1970
    as negative values for the birth date of the patient.

2004-09-17  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * CECAT7MainHeader.h: added missing enumeration values for the Patient
    Orientation header field.

2004-08-31  Hagen Mölle <draggore@gmx.de>

  * implemeted a Factory to support easier creation of supported fileformats
  * new fileformat: Concorde Micropet
  * new base class CMedIOData which defines a interface that should be
    implemented by all specific file classes
  * new base class CMedIOHeader which implements a intersection of all 
    supported headers
  * changed libmedio.pro.in to support new files  

2004-08-06  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * removed all inline based constructors and put them into
    their proper .cpp files to make the library interface
    a bit cleaner.

2004-08-05  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * added Q_EXPORT to all main classes to export them
    as shared library methods and changed layout of all
    header files a bit so that they are not wider than 77
    chars.

2004-08-04  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * removed scanner specific scanner.h from distribution as it
    was anyway just used to set some default values for the
    ECAT7 main headers.
  * added first "outsourced" version of the ecta6/7 and micropet
    aware input/output library which should carry more formats
    in future like DICOM/Interfile and so on.
